about.aboutText:
GTA Digital is a net label and Podcast series, set up by Gary The Apprentice, to provide the world with proper, underground Techno, staying clear of the more popular sound that is being churned out by bigger labels.

Here at GTA Digital, we are wanting to keep things real, releasing proper Techno, by proper Techno heads. We are always on the look out for new artists to get involved, so if you like what we are doing, and feel your music fits, please get in touch with a demo for us to consider releasing on the label.

This page will be used as our main platform for all of the Podcasts on the GTA Digital Podcast Series, if you would like to get involved, and provide a mix for the Podcast, please do get in touch.

To check out our full back catalogue of releases, to get information on the artists involved, and to check out the merchandise we have on sale.

podcasts.releaseInfoP1: Owen Ni is a musician, producer, DJ, and owner of the netlabel Run On Recordings. Starting in 2012, Owen has landed releases on well respected labels and has gained respect from countless artists in the game. His style drifts torwards a reminiscent sound of 90's Techno, normally labeled as Detroit Techno, and the lushness of Berlin based sub genre Dub Techno. Together, he uses these styles to create his own sound and style. Although you can generally expect Electronic music from Owen, his influences are vast. From Hip Hop to Classic Rock, Jazz to Film Scores, Owen finds listening to and appreciating different types of music as a way to learn and grow as an artist.

podcasts.releaseInfoP1: Lee Malice is the man behind The Lick, a techno event based in Fife, Scotland. The Lick is hosted in secret locations, and this year threw 3 All Nighter events in one of the most industrial locations that a techno party could be held in. These events have played host to acts such as Jamie Ball, Neil Landstrum, Hostage, Msstec plus loads of acts from the local Scottish underground techno scene, inlcuding myself.
podcasts.releaseInfoP2: The events that this boy has thrown have most definitely been the best I've played at since I started doing events in 2006. If you're in or around Central Scotland, keep an eye on The Lick and get yourself along to a future event.
podcasts.releaseInfoP3: Not only does Lee know how to put on a banging party, but he can also smash it behind the decks. Enjoy the next hour of straight bangers!

podcasts.releaseInfoP1: I'm very excited to present the 20th podcast in the GTA Digital Podcast Series, an hour of techno, performed live by myself, Gary The Apprentice. This is a massive achievement for me, having finally created and performed my very first live set just last month.
podcasts.releaseInfoP2: This set contains only my own music, broken apart and reconstructed live using Ableton, a Novation Launchpad and Launchcontrol XL.
podcasts.releaseInfoP3: This is a studio recording, with a couple of additional tracks added in which I did not include when performing this last month.
podcasts.releaseInfoP4: This also marks the launch of my own show on Fnoob Techno Radio GTA Digital Presents. It's been an awesome year for me music wise, landing a residency for an awesome techno event based in Fife, Scotland called The Lick, which has been absolutely banging, building and performing my very first live set and getting my own show on Fnoob. Thanks to everyone who has supported my music!

podcasts.releaseInfoP2: This month I decided to get back to it after two banging guests. I've recently been looking for some older style hard, driving, percussive techno, but with some groove to it. After hours of searching I managed to find loads of tracks in the style I was after, and in this mix you'll hear just a small portion of what I found.

releases.releaseInfoP1: This is what kicked off my venture into starting my own label. With being sick of too many label at the time churning out the same, boring generic techno, I decided to stop sending demos to labels and release my music on my own.
releases.releaseInfoP2: Expect 3 straight up banging techno tracks. Since releasing this EP the quality of my music has increased massively, but I'm still proud of these early tracks.
releases.releaseInfoP3: Pay what you want for this EP, or download it for free.

releases.releaseInfoP1: For our 9th release, we welcome Krowne to the team.
releases.releaseInfoP2: For this EP, Krowne has put together 2 very nice techno tracks, with label boss Gary The Apprentice on remix duties.
releases.releaseInfoP3: Expect deep grooving basslines, tribal percussion and twisted/hypnotic synths, with Gary The Apprentice taking the original tracks in his own direction and creating 2 solid remixes, with an oldskool twist.
releases.releaseInfoP4: There will be more coming from these two in the future, with some collab projects lined up, so be sure to keep a look out for other releases.

releases.releaseInfoP3: Pay what you want for this EP, or download it for free.

releases.releaseInfoP3: Pay what you want for this EP, or download it for free.

releases.releaseInfoP2: Expect to hear banging kicks, twisted, hypnotic synths & rolling percussion. The 4th track is something a bit different, this shows the more experimental side of what Gary creates.
releases.releaseInfoP3: Pay what you want for this EP, or download it for free.
releases.title: Mindfulness EP

releases.releaseInfoP1: So now onto our 14th release. After spending the last year in Holland, and not having a nice comfy setup to work in, not a lot went on music wise, but now Gary The Apprentice is back home in Edinburgh with a new home studio, and has put together some no messing around techno.
releases.releaseInfoP2: Expect to hear 3 straight up, straight forward, driving techno tracks, very much influenced by the older Techno sound, with the forth track Bon going in a completely different direction - a much more laid back/chilled out vibe, something for those Sunday chill out sessions.
releases.releaseInfoP3: Pay what you want for this EP, or download it for free.

releases.releaseInfoP1: For our first release of 2016, Gary The Apprentice is back with another 3 track EP.
releases.releaseInfoP2: For this release Gary has taken things in a slightly different direction, with slower BPM's, and more focus on percussive textures and low end grooves. Expect to hear rolling, hypnotic percussion, banging kick drums, grooving baselines and oldskool flavour synths.
